  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that having health care providers other than physicians within
      a &quot;Groupe de Médecine de Famille&quot; conduct cardiovascular risk assessments and teach lifestyle
      interventions to primary prevention patients will increase the likelihood that patients will
      adopt and maintain healthy lifestyles. These objectives will be supported by providing
      subjects with a cardiovascular risk profile estimating the subject's risk of cardiovascular
      disease and teaching them how to use the resources related to lifestyle changes available on
      the www.myhealthcheckup.com Web site.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
